43e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438|accessdate=2019-08-24}}</ref><ref name=mo2>{{cite web|title=\u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0442 \u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0445\u0440\u0430\u043c\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0436\u0451\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0421\u0438\u043b \u0420\u0424|url=https://function.mil.ru/news_page/country/more.htm?id=12204912@egNews|publisher=\u0414\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043c\u0443\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u041e|date=20 November 2018|accessdate=2019-08-24}} {{\u0421\u0432\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u043d\u043e|CC BY 4.0}}</ref>. The cathedral is being built with donations and budget funds from [[Moscow]] and the [[Moscow Oblast]]. Consecration will be held as part of the celebration of the 75th anniversary of Victory in the [[Great Patriotic War]]<ref>[http://redstar.ru/pomnit-istinnye-uroki-istorii/ \u041f\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0443\u0440\u043e\u043a\u0438 \u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0438 / \u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u00ab\u041a\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0437\u0432\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430\u00bb, 5 \u0444\u0435\u0432\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044f 2020]</ref>. An exhibition exposition dedicated to the [[History of Russia|history of the formation]] of the [[Russia|Russian state]] and its [[Russian Armed Forces|armed forces]] will be located on its territory.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0445\u0440\u0430\u043c \u0412\u043e\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0421\u0438\u043b \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u044f\u0442 \u0432 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u043a\u0435 \u00ab\u041f\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0438\u043e\u0442\u00bb|url=https://tvzvezda.ru/news/forces/content/201809041324-9v3w.htm|publisher=\u0417\u0432\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430|date=4 September 2018|accessdate=2019-08-24}}</ref>\n\n==Design==\nAccording to the official website, \u201cthe temple was designed in a monumental Russian style, organically incorporating modern architectural approaches and innovations unique to the Orthodox church creation\u201d. The facades of the building are finished with metal, the arches are glazed. The walls of the temple are decorated with murals with battle scenes from military history and scripture texts. The decoration of the lower (small) church is made of ceramics and decorated with [[Gzhel]] painting, and pieces of glass smalt were used in the manufacture of mosaic panels. The central apse dedicated to the Resurrection of Christ is made in the form of a metal relief. The decoration of the temple, the icon and the iconostasis are made of copper with enamels, as was done on the marching military icons. The vaults of the temple are collected from stained-glass windows depicting orders that were awarded for feats of arms in different periods of Russian history. The image of the Savior Not Made by Hands in the central dome of the temple is the largest image of the face of Christ executed in mosaic.\n\n===Sizes===\nThe height of the temple along with the cross according to the project will be 95 meters. The diameter of the drum of the main dome will be 19.45 meters. 1945 - the end of the Great Patriotic War. The height of the belfry will be 75 meters. In 2020, marks 75 years since the end of World War II. The height of the small dome is 14.18 meters. 1418 days and nights hostilities lasted in World War II.<ref name=mo/><ref name=mo2/> The area of the temple complex is 11 thousand m\u00b2. The capacity of the interior of the temple is up to 6 thousand people.\n===Bells===\nBells are made at the Voronezh Foundry. The decoration of the bells is based on ornaments that will decorate the cathedral.The bells reflect the theme of Victory in the [[Great Patriotic War]], icons of patrons of the Russian Army. The main bell-evangelist was decorated with bas-reliefs depicting key events of the [[Great Patriotic War]]. Work on the manufacture of bells was carried out for six months. The ensemble weighs more than 20 tons, it includes 18 bells, the largest of which weighs 10 tons.<ref name=mo3>{{cite web|title=\u041a\u043e\u043b\u043e\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430 \u0441 \u0438\u0437\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435\u043c \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u0432\u0438\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u0438 \u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u0432\u043e\u0439\u0441\u043a \u0443\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0438|url=https://function.mil.ru/news_page/country/more.htm?id=12248993@egNews|publisher=\u0414\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043c\u0443\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u041e|date=23 August 2019|accessdate=2019-08-24}} {{\u0421\u0432\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0434\u043d\u043e|CC BY 4.0}}</ref> 17 of the 18 bells are dedicated to the types and arms of the troops. On the one hand the emblem is applied to the bell, on the other, the image of the patron saint.<ref name=mo3/> On August 23, 2019 bells are set on the belfry of the cathedral.\n\n===Dome===\nOn November 15, 2019, a 80-ton central dome was erected on the cathedral, the height and diameter of which are 12 meters.<ref name=\"int\">{{cite web|title=\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0445\u0440\u0430\u043c \u0412\u043e\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0436\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u0441\u0438\u043b \u0420\u0424 \u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043a\u0443\u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u043c \u0432\u0435\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0432 80 \u0442\u043e\u043d\u043d|url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/684348|publisher=\u0418\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0444\u0430\u043a\u0441|date=2019-11-15|accessdate=2019-11-16}}</ref> In total, the cathedral has six domes, four of which are identical, each of which weighs 34 tons, the central one is the largest and one is on the belfry. The design has a high alloy steel frame with a strength factor from 300 to 1500 years.\n\n===Main icon===\n{{see also|Russian icons}}\nThe central [[Russian icons|icon]] of the Main Church of the Russian Armed Forces is the \u201cHoly Savior\u201d. The Icon of the Savior Not Made by Hands is a canonical image of the Holy Face of Jesus Christ, miraculously imprinted on a piece of material and transmitted by the Savior himself to the servant of Tsar Avgar V. The face on the icon surrounds the image of the Most Holy Mother of God of Kazan, Vladimir, Smolensk and Tikhvin, placed on artistic reliefs that depict significant events in the [[History of Russia|history of the Russian state]]. In the ark, which invariably accompanies the icon, there are eight particles of holy patrons: the great martyr George the Victorious, St. Andrew the First-Called, St. Nicholas the Wonderworker, St. Sergius of Radonezh, the great martyr Barbara, the apostle Peter, the great martyr Panteleimon the Healer, and also the righteous commander The Black Sea Fleet is one of the most revered saints in the fleet.\n\nThe image of the Savior is placed in a bronze fold and weighs about 100 kg. The icon itself without a fold has dimensions of about 98 \u00d7 84 \u00d7 10 cm.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Russia|Christianity}}\n*[[List of large Orthodox cathedrals]]\n*[[Eparchies of the Russian Orthodox Church]]\n*[[Russian Orthodox bell ringing]]\n*[[Russian icons]]\n*[[Persecution of Christians in the Soviet Union]]\n*[[Soviet anti-religious legislation]]\n*[[USSR anti-religious campaign (1917\u20131921)]]\n*[[USSR anti-religious campaign (1921\u20131928)]]\n*[[USSR anti-religious campaign (1958\u20131964)]]\n*[[USSR anti-religious campaign (1970s\u20131990)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat-inline|Main Cathedral of the Russian Armed Forces}}\n* [https://hram.mil.ru/ Website of the Main Cathedral of the Russian Armed Forces]\n* [https://foto.pamyat-naroda.ru/ \u0421\u0430\u0439\u0442 \u041f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u043a\u0442\u0430 \u041c\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u044b \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u00ab\u0414\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0433\u0430 \u043f\u0430\u043c\u044f\u0442\u0438\u00bb]\n\n[[Category:2020 establishments in Russia]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures under construction in Russia]]\n[[Category:Russian Ground Forces]]\n[[Category:Russian Orthodox cathedrals in Russia]]\n[[Category:Churches in Moscow Oblast]]\n[[Category:Churches completed in 2020]]\n[[Category:21st-century Eastern Orthodox church buildings]]\n[[Category:Odintsovsky District]]\n", "name_user": "KlingsorOfOz", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Cathedral_of_the_Russian_Armed_Forces"}
